00:15:57.320 --> 00:16:01.440
But here's the thing, if
you see afternoon light,

00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:04.580
you're going to adjust down
the sensitivity of your eyes

00:16:04.580 --> 00:16:08.010
so that you have a little
bit more wiggle room,

00:16:08.010 --> 00:16:09.880
a little bit more leeway

00:16:09.880 --> 00:16:13.630
to view lights from screens
and overhead lights even

00:16:13.630 --> 00:16:16.790
late at night without
disrupting your circadian clock.

00:16:16.790 --> 00:16:19.880
But it is a kind of a double-edged sword

00:16:19.880 --> 00:16:23.040
where you need a lot of
light early in the day

00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:26.590
and you need to avoid bright
lights later in the day.

